

=Bio=

"Liam Barrington-Bush is the author of ‘Anarchists in the Boardroom: How social media and social movements can help your organisation to be more like people.’ [www.morelikepeople.org/the-book] The book explores alternative organising approaches found within social movements around the globe and online, highlighting what they could mean for NGOs, charities and trade unions wanting to stay relevant in the 21st century. He was a joint-recipient of The Tyee (Canada) investigative journalism fellowship, with Jen Wilton in 2013, researching and writing a series on indigenous resistance to Canadian mining in Oaxaca, Mexico. 

Liam is a campaigner, facilitator, activist and writer, based in London, England, with working experience in Canada, Cuba, Mexico, Ukraine and Qatar."
(http://www.contributoria.com/issue/2015-09/55a2a44a1d70d5336c00010d/)

